news.title: Delhi LG directs DISCOMs to grant pending power connections in PM-UDAY colonies
news.para: PM-UDAY (Pradhan Mantri - Unauthorised Colonies in Delhi Awas Yojana) scheme is for recognition/conferment of ownership or transfer/mortgage to the residents of 1,731 unauthorised colonies benefitting around 40 lakh residents of Delhi.

news.title: PCB issues closure notice to two brick manufacturers in Indore
news.para: The brick manufacturing units, located in Bhangya village of Sanwer tehsil, Indore district, were found violating environmental norms during a thorough inspection conducted by the regional pollution control board team.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 335 crore worth assets of Unitech Group under PMLA
news.para: A provisional order has been issued under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) to attach movable properties valued at Rs 319 crore and Rs 16 crore belonging to Unitech International Realty Fund (UIRF) and Sahana Builders Private Limited.

news.title: Noida likely to see 30% hike in circle rate for residential areas
news.para: The proposal aims at increasing the circle rate by 25-30% in residential areas, 10% in industrial, commercial and IT sectors, and 15% in case of farmland.

news.title: ED attaches property worth Rs 56.86 crore of Krrish Realtech under PMLA
news.para: This action was taken in connection with the siphoning and illegal diversion of plot buyers’ money by accepting the same without having any licence from DTCP in its name.

news.title: Delhi: 900 sq yard-bungalow in Sunder Nagar sells for nearly Rs 100 crore
news.para: According to market sources, a bungalow at Sunder Nagar, owned by Sunil and Ravi Sachdev, has been sold for around Rs 96 crore.

news.title: Can Fin Homes' net profit up 33.79% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Can Fin Homes' net total income stood at Rs 962.69 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 10.52 per cent from Rs 871.03 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Evergrande says Shenzhen stock exchange imposed sanctions against unit, founder
news.para: The liquidators referred to a Shenzhen Stock Exchange document dated Sept. 30, which publicly reprimanded Hengda and Hui after the securities watchdog found Hengda had overstated revenue by 564 billion yuan ($79.20 billion) over two years through 2020 and fraudulence in its bond issuance.

news.title: Housr looks to cross Rs 150 crore revenue by March 2025
news.para: The company aims to hand over 11 to 12 properties currently in the pipeline along with foraying into new markets, including Chennai and Chandigarh, over the next three to four months.

news.title: Kajaria Ceramics' net profit dips 22.81% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Kajaria Ceramics' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,189.14 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 5.24 per cent from Rs 1,129.89 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Elan Group secures investment of Rs 1,200 crore from Kotak Real Estate Fund
news.para: The investment will be utilized as growth capital and strengthen its presence in Gurugram.

news.title: Land deal volume surge 65% in first nine months of 2024: Report
news.para: In January to September this year, Delhi-NCR led land deal activity with approximately 32% share, with Gurugram accounting for the highest land deal share at 65% and Noida and Greater Noida at 20%.

news.title: Over 200 new projects register with Uttar Pradesh RERA in Jan-Oct 2024
news.para: There has been a significant jump in the registration of new projects with Uttar Pradesh RERA in the non-NCR districts along with new project registration in the National Capital Region (NCR).

news.title: Goa’s beautiful land will become full of haphazard constructions: Bombay HC
news.para: The Bombay High Court at Goa has raised concerns over illegal constructions across the state, warning that inaction by authorities could lead to unplanned development. The court noted the failure of village panchayats to enforce laws and has called for legislative actions to curb this issue.

news.title: Mumbai court rejects bail plea of Punjalal G Dave Realtors partners in cheating case
news.para: The accused, including Maulik Dave, allegedly defrauded a 63-year-old Ghatkopar resident, Sanjay Dhawan, of Rs 3.91 crore under the pretext of investing in redevelopment projects.

news.title: Aditya Birla Real Estate posts net profit of Rs 2.82 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Aditya Birla Real Estate's total income stood at Rs 1,138.08 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 30.26 per cent from Rs 873.70 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Nisus Finance exits investment in Shriram Properties' Chirping Ridge, achieving 19% IRR
news.para: The Fund invested Rs 40 crore in Shriram Properties’ Chirping Ridge, a planned development project along with Jain Heights in Bangalore, in July 2022. It exited this investment within two years, securing a return of approximately 19% IRR.

news.title: SC permits centre-appointed Unitech board of seek police assistance to deal with disturbances
news.para: The top court had on January 20, 2020 come to the rescue of over 12,000 hassled homebuyers of Unitech Ltd by permitting the union ministry of corporate affairs to take "total management control" of the real estate firm and appointed retired Haryana cadre IAS officer Yudvir Singh Malik as chairman and managing director (CMD).

news.title: Jindal Group to expand cement capacity to 7 MnTPA with Rs 2,200 crore investment
news.para: Jindal Panther Cement (JPC) has commissioned the first cement grinding unit with a capacity of 1.5 MTPA, reinforcing commitment to low-carbon cement production. The facility will utilise about 1 MnTPA of blast furnace slag

news.title: Hotel Property urges shareholders to reject Charter Hall consortium takeover bid
news.para: The Australian firm said on Tuesday that the new offer from a group comprising Charter Hall's retail unit and pension fund Hostplus - which values it at A$755.8 million ($502.98 million) - materially undervalues its portfolio and that it is not compelling.
